# Robot protocol (the contract the brain calls)

Full reference: [docs/BRIDGE_PROTOCOL.md](mdc:docs/BRIDGE_PROTOCOL.md). Keep that doc in sync with code.

## Native <-> NativeRobotLink (stdio + fd3), inside the app

`ebo_bridge` (native, `autobot/robot/native/ebo_bridge.c`) talks to `NativeRobotLink`
(`autobot/robot/native_link.py`) over pipes:

- **Native -> link (stdout):** framed `[u32 len LE][u8 codec][payload]`
  - `codec 80` = HEVC video, `78` = H.264 video
  - `codec 0xFF` = inbound MAVLink status (battery/telemetry)
  - `codec 0xA0` = inbound audio (listen): payload `[codec_id:1][flags:1][G.711 data]`
- **link -> native (fd3):** framed `[u32 len LE][u8 kind][payload]`
  - `kind 0` = MAVLink over RDT (motor/dock/param/eyes)
  - `kind 1` = avSendIOCtrl: payload `[u16 io_type LE][data]`
  - `kind 2` = outbound audio (talkback): payload `[u8 codec_id][G.711 data]`  ŌåÉ Autobot addition

## MAVLink frames (built in `autobot/robot/frames.py` ŌĆö single source of truth)

- `motor_frame(ly, rx, lx, ry, buttons)` msgid 202, crc_extra 211. `ly>0` = forward (negated for the robot).
- `param_set_frame(group, key, value)` msgid 229, crc_extra 208. Used for toggles + eye animations.
- `command_frame(command)` msgid 200, crc_extra 196. e.g. `CMD_DOCK = 40154`.

Known params (`group/key`): `display/enable` (eyes), `video/night_vision`, `control/auto_avoidance`,
`control/fallarrest`, `security_patrol/enable`, `power/sleep`, and the eye-animation keys discovered in
`docs/BRIDGE_PROTOCOL.md` (e.g. `display/expression`). Unknown values are probed, never assumed.

## RobotLink (the in-process verbs; the ONLY way the brain touches the robot)

`autobot/robot/link.py` defines the contract; `NativeRobotLink` and `MockRobotLink` implement it. Methods
(async, returning JSON-able result dicts, fail-soft):

- `info()` / `telemetry()` ŌĆö connection/awake/codec/battery/toggles/eyes/audio summaries.
- `snapshot()` ŌĆö `(jpeg_bytes, error)`; `(None, reason)` while asleep / not ready.
- `move(ly, rx, duration)` ŌĆö timed move then auto-stop.
- `drive(ly, rx)` ŌĆö single continuous frame (the deadman stops the robot on silence).
- `stop()` ŌĆö immediate stop.
- `action(name)` ŌĆö wake|sleep|dock|undock|<toggle>_on|<toggle>_off|eyes_<anim>.
- `say_audio(g711, codec)` / `say_text(text)` ŌĆö talkback (also gated by the brain's talk toggle).
- `connection(state)` ŌĆö release/reclaim the single robot session for the Enabot app.
- `whep_upstream` / `hls_base` / `stream_auth_header()` ŌĆö video upstreams the web server proxies (None in mock).

Every method is best-effort and must never crash the app. `NativeRobotLink` keeps its OWN deadman watchdog
(`_drive_watchdog`): if `drive` frames stop arriving (~0.35s), it sends a stop frame regardless of the brain.
